TextBody:
Hi Frank,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix technical support. 

The "One Domain Controller per Domain" is a default host list that selects a DC based on a stored SQL procedure. This list can't be changed manually, however you can create a new list in the Host Management node, containing a DC for each domain that you'd like to query, and set the job group to use that host list. More information on Host Management can be found in our documentation here: https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/StealthAUDIT_11.5/page/Content/StealthAUDIT/Chapters/04.Host_Management/Host_Management_Activities.htm#_Add_Hosts

The warnings you're seeing on the 1-AD_Scan are related to custom attributes Netwrix is looking for out of the box. If the attributes listed in the warnings are not something you use or collect, you can either ignore the warnings (no affect on the scan) or you can remove the offending attributes following this article: https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/z-kb-articles-salesforce/page/kA0Qk0000000divKAA.html

As for the Activity Events, let's set up a remote session to take a look:
https://nwxcorp.my.salesforce-sites.com/cts?Id=FZOnXw2zheBNLGdwf4bYNgBteVCItKHRyPYGVLgRXqY-Z&MeetingID=JUfZ8PQkTsG4CnzapxbyCpWyo_kfHLdA3vEqozreglQ-Z

Thank you,

Tay Caliguiri

Senior Technical Support Engineer

TextBody:
Hey Frank,

Thank you for meeting with us this morning. To recap our session, we:

	Found that the new NetApp paths are slightly different than previously, leading us to believe there may be some missing permissions on the NetApp that got lost during the transition
	Ran an FSAA scan at level 0 depth and received an access denied error


Please have your NetApp team review the permissions on the NetApp host (link below, we recommend Method 2) and then send us a screenshot of what the shares looks like in Computer Management. We will then be able to compare that with what we have in the AIC to see if they match or not. If they don't match, we may need to drop/archive data and run a fresh scan.
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/Config/NetAppCMode/Access.htm

Let me know if you have any questions!

Thank you,

Tay Caliguiri

Senior Technical Support Engineer
